        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 1:06AM CDT by NWS Hastings NE</headline>
        <description>At 106 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Grafton, or 14 miles south of York, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Fairmont around 110 AM CDT.
Exeter around 115 AM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT for
south central and east central Nebraska.</instruction>
